.SH NAME
xbc_node_compose_key_after \- Compose partial key string of the XBC node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xbc_node_compose_key_after
.BI "(struct xbc_node *root "  ","
.BI "struct xbc_node *node "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "root" 12
Root XBC node
.IP "node" 12
Target XBC node.
.IP "buf" 12
A buffer to store the key.
.IP "size" 12
The size of the \fIbuf\fP.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Compose the partial key of the \fInode\fP into \fIbuf\fP, which is starting right
after \fIroot\fP (\fIroot\fP is not included.) If \fIroot\fP is NULL, this returns full
key words of \fInode\fP.
Returns the total length of the key stored in \fIbuf\fP. Returns -EINVAL
if \fInode\fP is NULL or \fIroot\fP is not the ancestor of \fInode\fP or \fIroot\fP is \fInode\fP,
or returns -ERANGE if the key depth is deeper than max depth.
This is expected to be used with \fBxbc_find_node\fP to list up all (child)
keys under given key.
